      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAJOR ART NZ (1) drew wider and worked when tackling stronger company at Menangle last start but had looked close to a win prior, kicking off in Australia with four successive seconds. Very well placed in this line-up and the ace draw can see him deliver his first win on Aussie shores. BLACK ONYX (7) showed improvement and didn't do a bad job when beaten 6m into fifth at this venue last time out. Draws for a trail and should be fitter again third-up so can progress further. LIGHT ME UP NZ (3) has been coming from wider barriers of late so could show his best from this draw. FIRE FOX NZ (9) draws on the second line but hasn't been far away of late. Can be competitive again.",
